[MK] case called at 10:44am.
Defendant Jeremy Dorsey in court with Attorney Karl E Huebner.  ADA Jeffrey Shock appears for the State of Wisconsin.  
Service of the Amended Criminal Complaint is affirmed; reading is waived. 
The Court clarifies that only Count #2 applies to Mr. Dorsey.  
Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; plea of " No Contest" entered on Count #2; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; the Court accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

On Count #2, the Court withholds sentence, and places Mr. Dorsey on Probation for one year, with conditions:

--to undergo AODA assessment and follow through with recommended treatment as directed by the Agent 
--to undergo assessment, treatment, therapy and counseling as required by the Agent
--to be subject to random drug screening
--no possession or consumption of any controlled substances without a valid prescription
--no contact with any known drug offender except for treatment purposes as deemed appropriate by the Agent
--to pay the $50 in drug testing fees 
--to comply with DNA sample provision upon demand
--to obtain/maintain employment and/or education program as approved by the Agent
--to pay costs and surcharges
